replies.text:
You can't combine function declarations in this way, but you can create a wrapper function that calls all three functions at once:

public void Attack() { Debug.Log(name + " is attacking");
public void Spell() { Debug.Log(name + " is casting a spell");
public void Damage() { Debug.Log(name + " caused damage");
public void SpellAttack() {
  Attack();
  Spell();
  Damage();
}
// now you can just call SpellAttack to do all 3

