For anyone wondering about the above - firstly there's no reason not to prevent rotation using the above method (in fact the instructor goes on to do this very thing later in the video), however if you have a reason to do it in code (perhaps you want to freeze and unfreeze rotation based on some game mechanic), you can do it using RigigbodyConstraints2D.FreezeRotation, something like this:

  myBody = GetComponent<Rigidbody2D>();

  myBody.constraints = RigidbodyConstraints2D.FreezeRotation;

